    <!-- Page 8: Key Findings & Implications -->
    <div class="page">
        <div class="section-tag">Key Findings & Research Implications</div>
        
        <div style="background: #4A5D3A; color: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 25px;">
            <h3 style="color: #D4AF37; margin-top: 0; font-size: 18px;">Critical Research Gaps</h3>
            <div style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6;">
                Our literature review reveals significant opportunities for contribution to the field of accessible heritage design, particularly in the context of historic houses and period-specific environments.
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="intro-columns">
            <div>
                <h4 style="color: #4A5D3A; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 15px;">Identified Opportunities</h4>
                
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #D4AF37; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    <h5 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; color: #4A5D3A; font-size: 12px;">Historic House Context</h5>
                    <p style="font-size: 10px; margin: 0; line-height: 1.5;">Limited research specifically addresses accessibility challenges in 18th-century heritage environments, where conservation requirements constrain technological interventions.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #D4AF37; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    <h5 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; color: #4A5D3A; font-size: 12px;">SEND School Groups</h5>
                    <p style="font-size: 10px; margin: 0; line-height: 1.5;">Existing studies focus primarily on individual visitors, with insufficient attention to group dynamics and educational contexts for neurodiverse learners.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #D4AF37; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    <h5 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; color: #4A5D3A; font-size: 12px;">Rural Heritage Sites</h5>
                    <p style="font-size: 10px; margin: 0; line-height: 1.5;">Most accessibility research focuses on urban museums, potentially overlooking unique challenges faced by heritage sites in rural locations like Russborough.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div>
                <h4 style="color: #4A5D3A; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 15px;">Design Principles for Russborough</h4>
                
                <p style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    Based on our literature synthesis, we propose the following evidence-based design principles for enhancing accessibility at Russborough House:
                </p>
                
                <ol style="font-size: 10px; line-height: 1.6; padding-left: 15px;">
                    <li><strong>Contextual Personalization:</strong> Leverage AI to adapt content and interaction modes based on individual visitor profiles and preferences.</li>
                    
                    <li><strong>Multi-Modal Engagement:</strong> Combine visual, auditory, and haptic feedback to accommodate diverse sensory processing needs.</li>
                    
                    <li><strong>Preparation and Predictability:</strong> Provide advance virtual experiences to reduce anxiety and support visit planning for neurodiverse visitors.</li>
                    
                    <li><strong>Flexible Pacing:</strong> Design self-guided experiences that allow visitors to control timing and depth of engagement.</li>
                    
                    <li><strong>Social Consideration:</strong> Address group dynamics and peer support mechanisms for school visits and family groups.</li>
                </ol>
                
                <div style="background: #D4AF37; color: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 6px; margin-top: 20px;">
                    <h5 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; font-size: 12px;">Next Phase Research Questions</h5>
                    <p style="font-size: 10px; margin: 0; line-height: 1.4;">How can digital accessibility solutions be authentically integrated into historic house environments while maintaining period atmosphere and supporting diverse learning needs?</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="page-footer">
            <div>IMPLICATIONS FOR PRACTICE â€¢ RESEARCH GAPS IDENTIFIED</div>
